//
// ConvolutionTest.params

// A params file to test convolution. There is a 16-by-32-by-8 input layer, and
// a 64-by-64-by-1 output layer, and an 8-by-8-by-1 shared weights connection with 8 kernels.
// Each weight patch is periodic in x with period 4, and periodic in y with period 2.
// Each 4-by-2 subsection of the patch has 7 weights of value 0 and 1 weight of value 1.
// The location of the nonzero weight is given by the data-patch index, as follows:
//     +---------+
//     | 0 1 2 3 |
//     | 4 5 6 7 |
//     +---------+
// The patch with data-patch index k has nonzero weight in location k, and zero weight
// in the other seven locations.
//
// The required margins are 1 in the x-direction and 2 in the y-direction. The result in
// the output layer is periodic in x with period 4 and periodic in y with period 2. The
// 4-by-2 section in the upper left corner is
//     +-------------+
//     | 56 64 40 48 |
//     | 24 32  8 16 |
//     +-------------+

